subject:

THE GIFT OF GRACE
===================================================================
verse:

For by grace you have been save through faith, And that not
of yourselves; it is a gift of God, not of works, lest
anyone should boast. (Eph. 2:8,9)

===================================================================
reflection:

What Paul is really saying in these two verses is; “we are
saved by grace alone, through faith alone, in Christ alone.”
Our works should be out of appreciation for what Christ has
done for us. I am reminded of what a friend once said to me;

“Remember we can never out give God, He has a bigger
shovel.”


===================================================================
prayer:

Gracious God, thank You that we are saved by grace alone,
through faith alone, in Christ alone. Let my works flow not
from striving but from gratitude for all Jesus has done.
Teach me generosity that mirrors Your heart—trusting that we
can never outgive You, for Your shovel is always bigger.
Fill me with joy to serve, give, and love for Your glory.
Amen. (AI)

